# ==============================
# FIREBASE FIRESTORE RULES
# ==============================

- Firestore is used ONLY for realtime UI
- SQL is source of truth

---

Structure:

chats/{conversationId}/messages/{messageId}

Fields:
- senderId
- role ("user" | "ai" | "teacher" | "student")
- text
- createdAt

---

Rules:

- Firestore auto-creates collections → DO NOT manually create
- ALWAYS use consistent conversationId

---

Conversation ID rules:

- AI chat:
    ai-{userId}

- User chat:
    chat-{user1}-{user2}

---

# ==============================
# FRONTEND RULES (React)
# ==============================

- NEVER duplicate messages
- NEVER mix API + Firestore incorrectly

---

# Message handling:

- When sending:
    setMessages → add user message ONCE

- After API:
    setMessages → add AI message ONCE

---

# History loading:

- MUST use:
    setMessages(res.data)

- MUST NOT use:
    setMessages(prev => [...prev, ...res.data])

---

# Firestore:

- If using onSnapshot:
    → DO NOT use API history at same time

